</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6700/sound-volume-not-displaying-the-correct-popup/?comment=6701#comment-6701</link><description>No, it's not an i3 issue. I guess you have a daemon like dunst running to display those messages. They are sent by volumeicon (unless your keybinding does it, but that you'd hopefully be aware of then). I know that dunst doesn't support the full notification standard, maybe that's an issue.</description><pubDate>Sat, 26 Sep 2015 20:00:51 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6700/sound-volume-not-displaying-the-correct-popup/?comment=6701#comment-6701</guid></item></channel></rss>